Small correction:Water with one proton missing (leaving its electron behind) that would be a negativly charged hydroxide ion. Water with one hydrogen missing, including the electron, that would be a hydroxyl radical. It has no charge but a highly reactive unpaired electron. Greetings from rainy Berlin
